This License governs the use, reproduction, and distribution of the DaoTi
(道体) Foundation Model, comprising two categories of assets defined below.

本许可证管辖道体基础模型的使用、复制和分发。该模型包含以下两类资产。


1. DEFINITIONS | 定义
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1.1 "Reference Code" means the software source files defining the model
    architecture, module interfaces, and data structures, including but not
    limited to yijing_v53_model.py, verify_release.py, and yijing_v53_config.json.

    "参考代码" 指定义模型架构、模块接口和数据结构的软件源文件，包括但不限于
    yijing_v53_model.py、verify_release.py 和 yijing_v53_config.json。

1.2 "Documentation" means the written materials describing the theoretical
    foundations, training methodology, experimental results, and system design,
    including but not limited to the Whitepaper and Papers directories.

    "文档" 指描述理论基础、训练方法、实验结果和系统设计的书面材料，包括但不限于
    白皮书和论文目录。

1.3 "Model Weights" means the trained numerical parameters of the DaoTi
    Foundation Model in any format (including but not limited to .safetensors,
    .pt, .pth, .bin, .onnx), the SHA256 verification files associated with
    them, and any derivative models created through fine-tuning, distillation,
    or transfer learning based on the original weights.

    "模型权重" 指道体基础模型在任何格式下的训练数值参数（包括但不限于
    .safetensors、.pt、.pth、.bin、.onnx），以及与之关联的 SHA256 校验文件，
    以及基于原始权重通过微调、蒸馏或迁移学习产生的任何衍生模型。

1.4 "Academic Use" means use by an accredited educational or research
    institution for non-commercial research, teaching, or scholarly publication.
    Use by research divisions of commercial entities does not qualify as
    Academic Use.

    "学术用途" 指经认证的教育或研究机构为非商业研究、教学或学术发表目的而使用。
    商业实体的研究部门使用不构成学术用途。

1.5 "Commercial Use" means any use that generates revenue or provides
    competitive advantage in a commercial context, including but not limited to:
    (a) integration into a product or service offered for sale or subscription;
    (b) use as a component of a revenue-generating system;
    (c) use by a for-profit entity in its operations;
    (d) provision of model inference as a service (MaaS).

    "商业用途" 指在商业背景下产生收入或提供竞争优势的任何使用，包括但不限于：
    (a) 集成至销售或订阅形式提供的产品或服务中；
    (b) 作为营利系统的组成部分使用；
    (c) 由营利性实体在其运营中使用；
    (d) 以模型推理即服务(MaaS)形式提供。


